1
00:00:10,800 --> 00:00:13,080
If it weren't for
the annual health checkup,

2
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:14,380
would I ever get to see you guys?

3
00:00:15,300 --> 00:00:17,290
If North hadn't forced me,
I wouldn't have come.

4
00:00:17,530 --> 00:00:19,510
Yeah, they wouldn't find anything anyway.

5
00:00:19,740 --> 00:00:21,680
And even if they did,
I still wouldn't get treated.

6
00:00:22,100 --> 00:00:23,100
I'm Arthit, for fuck's sake.

7
00:00:23,670 --> 00:00:24,920
I'm not gonna die that easily.

8
00:00:26,100 --> 00:00:27,420
Mm, true.

9
00:00:27,960 --> 00:00:28,840
Cute, huh?

10
00:00:30,610 --> 00:00:30,930
Huh?

11
00:00:31,610 --> 00:00:32,840
I mean, Typhoon is.

12
00:00:33,300 --> 00:00:35,290
It was his idea to talk to everyone

13
00:00:35,760 --> 00:00:36,990
to force all of you guys

14
00:00:37,010 --> 00:00:39,120
to get a checkup at my hospital.

15
00:00:39,340 --> 00:00:41,300
Not only does he care about me,

16
00:00:41,410 --> 00:00:43,020
but he also cares about
the people around me.

17
00:00:43,970 --> 00:00:45,040
How freaking cute.

18
00:00:45,470 --> 00:00:46,100
Don't you think?

19
00:00:46,130 --> 00:00:47,000
Wait, wait, wait...

20
00:00:47,370 --> 00:00:48,800
Are you gonna show off your boyfriend

21
00:00:49,270 --> 00:00:50,520
just like that?

22
00:00:50,710 --> 00:00:51,200
What?

23
00:00:51,890 --> 00:00:53,660
Well, it's true.

24
00:00:53,760 --> 00:00:55,090
There are dozens of
hospitals in Chiang Mai,

25
00:00:55,170 --> 00:00:56,880
and you had me come all the way
to Bangkok for a checkup?

26
00:00:57,030 --> 00:00:57,550
Yeah.

27
00:00:57,580 --> 00:00:58,960
Man, keep that cuteness to yourself.

28
00:00:59,070 --> 00:01:00,260
What a fucking hassle for us.

29
00:01:00,300 --> 00:01:00,760
True.

30
00:01:00,790 --> 00:01:02,490
Everyone's moved to Bangkok,

31
00:01:02,650 --> 00:01:04,160
- except you two.
- Huh?

32
00:01:04,320 --> 00:01:05,400
So I'm the problem now?

33
00:01:05,730 --> 00:01:08,020
I was minding my own business
when you guys decided to move away.

34
00:01:08,100 --> 00:01:10,920
Well, Typhoon works on film sets,

35
00:01:11,510 --> 00:01:12,990
so I figured it'd be most convenient

36
00:01:13,370 --> 00:01:14,390
to move down here.

37
00:01:14,790 --> 00:01:16,230
So you proposed to the board

38
00:01:16,250 --> 00:01:18,300
to open a new branch here?

39
00:01:18,740 --> 00:01:21,300
You used that as
an excuse to move him here,

40
00:01:21,400 --> 00:01:22,010
that's it?

41
00:01:22,500 --> 00:01:24,420
Well, he's the considerate type.

42
00:01:24,650 --> 00:01:26,700
If he'd known it was for personal reasons,

43
00:01:27,520 --> 00:01:28,360
he wouldn't have come.

44
00:01:29,980 --> 00:01:30,720
Dude,

45
00:01:31,260 --> 00:01:32,580
that excuse

46
00:01:32,910 --> 00:01:34,310
cost you nine figures, though.

47
00:01:35,950 --> 00:01:37,080
It's actually not that much.

48
00:01:38,050 --> 00:01:39,450
I had business partners.

49
00:01:43,310 --> 00:01:46,200
Easter had to extern
at a clinic in Bangkok.

50
00:01:46,710 --> 00:01:48,290
Do you expect me to let him come alone?

51
00:01:49,440 --> 00:01:50,280
Besides,

52
00:01:50,700 --> 00:01:52,890
I only bought a small stake with Tonfah

53
00:01:53,050 --> 00:01:54,000
as an excuse.

54
00:01:54,090 --> 00:01:54,800
Jeez...

55
00:01:54,840 --> 00:01:56,610
We'll move back as soon as
Easter finishes his externship.

56
00:02:01,340 --> 00:02:02,100
What're you looking at?

57
00:02:03,300 --> 00:02:05,280
I'm the only one
who doesn't leave you behind.

58
00:02:05,360 --> 00:02:07,370
You fly to San Francisco
every other weekend.

59
00:02:07,420 --> 00:02:08,480
That's not leaving me behind?

60
00:02:08,850 --> 00:02:09,490
Well...

61
00:02:09,930 --> 00:02:11,550
I'm an artist, Johan.

62
00:02:12,010 --> 00:02:13,640
Damn it, when you write music and shit,

63
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:14,820
you need feelings.

64
00:02:14,940 --> 00:02:16,600
The right feelings and emotions, get it?

65
00:02:16,750 --> 00:02:18,850
Yeah! Plus,

66
00:02:19,660 --> 00:02:20,720
Daotok likes it there too.

67
00:02:21,130 --> 00:02:23,220
There's no reason not to fly him there.

68
00:02:23,260 --> 00:02:25,130
Alright, alright, stop it.

69
00:02:25,820 --> 00:02:26,910
By the way, Johan,

70
00:02:27,360 --> 00:02:29,420
how's North doing?

71
00:02:30,380 --> 00:02:31,310
Has he been doing well?

72
00:02:36,410 --> 00:02:38,090
It's weeks away
until your externship,

73
00:02:38,120 --> 00:02:39,840
yet you chose to leave me, Easter.

74
00:02:40,010 --> 00:02:42,040
Ugh, come on, North.

75
00:02:42,230 --> 00:02:44,800
Hill wants me
to get familiar with the place.

76
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:45,490
Here,

77
00:02:45,750 --> 00:02:47,700
after I finish my externship,
I'll come right back.

78
00:02:47,730 --> 00:02:49,600
I'm not gonna be here forever or anything.

79
00:02:50,200 --> 00:02:51,780
Maew, don't give me that smile.

80
00:02:52,130 --> 00:02:53,200
You're the real punk.

81
00:02:54,020 --> 00:02:55,890
Well, I have to work, North.

82
00:02:56,010 --> 00:02:57,010
Don't be mad, alright?

83
00:02:57,240 --> 00:02:58,730
Whenever Tonfah is free,

84
00:02:58,840 --> 00:03:00,240
I'll make time to come see you.

85
00:03:00,370 --> 00:03:00,900
Ugh!

86
00:03:01,150 --> 00:03:02,910
You're the first to leave me.

87
00:03:06,060 --> 00:03:07,160
Don't get mad so quickly.

88
00:03:07,880 --> 00:03:09,810
There's something else
to get even madder about!

89
00:03:10,780 --> 00:03:11,780
Look!

90
00:03:12,160 --> 00:03:12,980
Hi, North.

91
00:03:13,490 --> 00:03:14,910
What?! Daotok?

92
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:16,840
Are you back from San Francisco?

93
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:18,000
Since when?

94
00:03:18,320 --> 00:03:19,100
Mm...

95
00:03:19,280 --> 00:03:20,930
Since yesterday.

96
00:03:21,050 --> 00:03:22,610
And you chose to go see them

97
00:03:23,010 --> 00:03:24,480
instead of me?

98
00:03:24,630 --> 00:03:25,790
Damn it.

99
00:03:25,830 --> 00:03:27,000
Does no one love me anymore?

100
00:03:27,330 --> 00:03:29,200
Arthit has something
to take care of in Bangkok.

101
00:03:29,450 --> 00:03:31,360
Once he's done, I'll be back with you.

102
00:03:31,440 --> 00:03:32,520
Save it!

103
00:03:35,710 --> 00:03:37,810
No one loves me anymore...

104
00:03:46,190 --> 00:03:47,120
Uh, Johan!

105
00:03:47,150 --> 00:03:48,310
I do.

106
00:03:48,460 --> 00:03:49,130
Hm?

107
00:03:49,870 --> 00:03:50,490
My friends!

108
00:03:53,000 --> 00:03:54,240
Hello, Johan.

109
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:55,400
Hello.

110
00:03:57,500 --> 00:03:58,320
Johan!

111
00:03:58,640 --> 00:03:59,500
This is embarrassing!

112
00:03:59,850 --> 00:04:00,560
- What?
- What?

113
00:04:02,090 --> 00:04:03,120
What's up with him?

114
00:04:05,100 --> 00:04:05,780
So...

115
00:04:06,220 --> 00:04:07,420
who didn't love you earlier?

116
00:04:08,350 --> 00:04:09,720
It was nothing, Johan.

117
00:04:09,930 --> 00:04:11,590
I was just messing with them

118
00:04:11,980 --> 00:04:14,410
since they're all together in Bangkok.

119
00:04:15,140 --> 00:04:15,890
I had to be...

120
00:04:16,320 --> 00:04:17,710
a little upset.

121
00:04:18,480 --> 00:04:20,410
Then do you want to see them?

122
00:04:20,490 --> 00:04:21,250
I can take you there.

123
00:04:21,280 --> 00:04:22,600
Oh, it's fine, Johan.

124
00:04:22,850 --> 00:04:24,790
Just the video call will do.

125
00:04:24,980 --> 00:04:25,910
It'd be a waste of money.

126
00:04:30,580 --> 00:04:33,560
So North is serious
about becoming a game caster?

127
00:04:33,630 --> 00:04:36,010
Mm, he's been playing video games and...

128
00:04:36,650 --> 00:04:38,470
making cute faces for me every day.

129
00:04:40,430 --> 00:04:41,510
What a showoff.

130
00:04:41,550 --> 00:04:42,350
Yeah.

131
00:04:42,750 --> 00:04:43,750
By the way,

132
00:04:44,510 --> 00:04:46,390
Typhoon's been saying he misses North.

133
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:47,790
Maybe...

134
00:04:48,430 --> 00:04:50,210
we should find some time to eat together?

135
00:04:51,080 --> 00:04:52,080
Damn it...

136
00:04:52,520 --> 00:04:55,850
It took a health checkup just to
get four of us to even meet up.

137
00:04:56,420 --> 00:04:56,780
True.

138
00:04:56,820 --> 00:04:58,520
Our schedules barely align.

139
00:04:58,810 --> 00:05:01,310
Plus, Johan and North live so far away.

140
00:05:01,700 --> 00:05:02,500
Mm...

141
00:05:02,550 --> 00:05:03,910
Right, Johan. I'm sorry

142
00:05:04,500 --> 00:05:05,690
Easter had to move here
earlier than expected.

143
00:05:06,310 --> 00:05:08,310
I wanted to give him time to adjust
before he starts at the clinic.

144
00:05:08,590 --> 00:05:09,590
Why be sorry?

145
00:05:09,740 --> 00:05:10,800
Everyone's fine.

146
00:05:11,230 --> 00:05:11,810
Yeah.

147
00:05:11,850 --> 00:05:13,820
Well, Easter said
he was worried about North,

148
00:05:14,140 --> 00:05:15,010
that he'd be lonely.

149
00:05:15,700 --> 00:05:17,410
They were inseparable back in Chiang Mai.

150
00:05:17,770 --> 00:05:18,490
Why would he be lonely?

151
00:05:18,680 --> 00:05:19,680
He has me.

152
00:05:21,730 --> 00:05:22,580
Johan,

153
00:05:23,790 --> 00:05:25,000
a boyfriend and a friend

154
00:05:25,470 --> 00:05:26,760
are two different things.

155
00:05:35,210 --> 00:05:36,040
Johan.

156
00:05:39,150 --> 00:05:39,630
Johan!

157
00:05:39,900 --> 00:05:40,710
Yes?

158
00:05:42,370 --> 00:05:43,100
Is there...

159
00:05:43,930 --> 00:05:45,220
something on your mind?

160
00:05:45,420 --> 00:05:46,420
You seem stressed.

161
00:05:47,810 --> 00:05:49,110
No, it's nothing.

162
00:05:49,120 --> 00:05:50,350
Just a bit lost in thought.

163
00:05:50,510 --> 00:05:51,700
You sure?

164
00:05:52,180 --> 00:05:53,710
You can tell me anything.

165
00:05:58,180 --> 00:05:59,370
Are you free next week?

166
00:06:01,020 --> 00:06:02,620
There's a place I want to take you to.

167
00:06:05,320 --> 00:06:07,150
[Porawut Phatthanapatsri]
[CHIEF EXECUTIVE OFFICER]

168
00:06:12,820 --> 00:06:14,330
It's lunchtime,

169
00:06:14,350 --> 00:06:15,440
Doctor.

170
00:06:17,660 --> 00:06:18,410
Typhoon?

171
00:06:18,740 --> 00:06:19,790
What brings you here?

172
00:06:20,140 --> 00:06:21,310
Well...

173
00:06:21,870 --> 00:06:22,930
filming is on a break.

174
00:06:23,230 --> 00:06:24,590
Setting up a new scene will take two hours.

175
00:06:24,820 --> 00:06:26,920
Since I'm free, I thought...

176
00:06:27,140 --> 00:06:28,670
I'd come have lunch with you.

177
00:06:29,460 --> 00:06:30,150
Is that so?

178
00:06:30,900 --> 00:06:31,750
That's so sweet.

179
00:06:43,790 --> 00:06:44,710
Are you tired?

180
00:06:45,020 --> 00:06:46,100
I'm exhausted.

181
00:06:46,570 --> 00:06:48,310
I could use some cheering up.

182
00:06:53,820 --> 00:06:54,550
Mm.

183
00:06:54,810 --> 00:06:56,160
I feel better now.

184
00:06:56,600 --> 00:06:57,920
How did you do that?

185
00:06:58,590 --> 00:07:00,600
I didn't do anything...

186
00:07:04,930 --> 00:07:06,280
I actually feel better.

187
00:07:14,970 --> 00:07:15,700
Take this.

188
00:07:17,400 --> 00:07:18,470
Why?

189
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:48,190
Why didn't you wait for me to pick you up?

190
00:07:50,180 --> 00:07:51,590
I was just walking around the mall.

191
00:07:52,610 --> 00:07:53,990
Since the hospital is nearby

192
00:07:55,310 --> 00:07:57,630
and you're about to finish your shift,

193
00:07:58,720 --> 00:08:00,620
I thought it might be faster
if we went back together.

194
00:08:01,170 --> 00:08:02,500
You've grown a lot.

195
00:08:02,930 --> 00:08:03,880
Of course.

196
00:08:04,550 --> 00:08:06,680
I'm a grown-up now,
not a two-year-old.

197
00:08:06,960 --> 00:08:08,320
Well, you'll always

198
00:08:08,670 --> 00:08:10,000
a two-year-old in my eyes.

199
00:08:14,600 --> 00:08:16,920
So Dr. Hill's slacking off here
with his boyfriend, huh?

200
00:08:17,330 --> 00:08:18,190
No wonder

201
00:08:18,380 --> 00:08:20,230
I couldn't find him in his department.

202
00:08:20,510 --> 00:08:21,710
Hey, watch it,

203
00:08:21,940 --> 00:08:23,280
President.

204
00:08:23,490 --> 00:08:25,240
I'm off work, not slacking off.

205
00:08:26,540 --> 00:08:27,360
Sure.

206
00:08:27,990 --> 00:08:29,480
Hill, Easter,
do you want to come eat with us?

207
00:08:29,820 --> 00:08:31,170
We're just about to go.

208
00:08:31,300 --> 00:08:31,810
Yes!

209
00:08:31,970 --> 00:08:32,620
Yeah?

210
00:08:33,030 --> 00:08:33,720
Can we?

211
00:08:34,680 --> 00:08:35,330
Okay.

212
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:36,520
- Let's go.
- Let's go then.

213
00:08:36,650 --> 00:08:37,230
Let's go!

214
00:08:41,700 --> 00:08:42,470
Thank you.

215
00:08:44,590 --> 00:08:46,210
Since most of us are here...

216
00:08:46,400 --> 00:08:48,890
Maew and I wanted to ask for your advice.

217
00:08:50,660 --> 00:08:52,100
Yes, what is it?

218
00:08:54,090 --> 00:08:54,780
What?!

219
00:08:54,980 --> 00:08:57,440
I'm talking about us going to
Chiang Mai to visit North.

220
00:08:58,130 --> 00:08:59,110
Oh, yes.

221
00:08:59,530 --> 00:09:02,910
I'm starting my externship soon,
so I won't have much time.

222
00:09:03,140 --> 00:09:04,780
So we want to go

223
00:09:04,830 --> 00:09:06,190
to Chiang Mai to visit North.

224
00:09:06,590 --> 00:09:09,150
I'm not sure if you guys are free...

225
00:09:12,770 --> 00:09:13,720
I don't think...

226
00:09:13,880 --> 00:09:15,640
we need to go all the way to Chiang Mai.

227
00:09:18,520 --> 00:09:19,520
How come?

228
00:09:22,750 --> 00:09:23,820
Where are we going?

229
00:09:25,390 --> 00:09:26,710
Where are you taking me, Johan?

230
00:09:28,990 --> 00:09:29,800
Johan...

231
00:09:31,980 --> 00:09:32,720
Johan?

232
00:09:36,760 --> 00:09:37,410
Whoa!

233
00:09:38,350 --> 00:09:38,990
Do you like it?

234
00:09:41,360 --> 00:09:42,560
Did you get these for me?

235
00:09:42,800 --> 00:09:44,430
It's all brand new.

236
00:09:44,870 --> 00:09:45,870
Wow...

237
00:09:47,040 --> 00:09:48,040
I didn't just buy you this PC set,

238
00:09:49,540 --> 00:09:50,790
I also got you this condo.

239
00:09:50,890 --> 00:09:51,610
Huh?!

240
00:09:56,440 --> 00:09:58,900
Hill said you were in Bangkok.

241
00:09:58,970 --> 00:10:00,930
Yeah, I just got here this evening.

242
00:10:00,970 --> 00:10:04,640
I spoke to Maew about
visiting you in Chiang Mai.

243
00:10:04,810 --> 00:10:07,070
So we don't have to go that far now, right?

244
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:08,110
Exactly.

245
00:10:08,260 --> 00:10:09,600
Hey, shall we go to the beach?

246
00:10:09,780 --> 00:10:10,920
I feel like going.

247
00:10:11,070 --> 00:10:13,370
Alright, I'll let you decide for this trip

248
00:10:13,400 --> 00:10:14,640
as an apology

249
00:10:14,650 --> 00:10:17,290
for leaving you alone in Chiang Mai for so long.

250
00:10:17,340 --> 00:10:18,120
Who was alone?

251
00:10:18,920 --> 00:10:19,700
Me?

252
00:10:20,180 --> 00:10:21,980
I've got Johan in every breath I take.

253
00:10:22,260 --> 00:10:23,970
Ugh, whatever.

254
00:10:24,120 --> 00:10:27,420
Anyway, why did Johan
suddenly buy a condo in Bangkok?

255
00:10:27,460 --> 00:10:28,770
Hm...

256
00:10:29,210 --> 00:10:30,010
I...

257
00:10:30,470 --> 00:10:31,610
haven't asked him yet.

258
00:10:31,900 --> 00:10:33,220
But I'll ask him soon.

259
00:10:35,420 --> 00:10:37,150
What?! 15 million?!

260
00:10:37,420 --> 00:10:37,920
Well...

261
00:10:38,420 --> 00:10:41,760
This condo is between
Tonfah's house and Hill's condo.

262
00:10:42,020 --> 00:10:42,700
I just...

263
00:10:43,320 --> 00:10:46,480
want you to be able to
meet your friends easily.

264
00:10:47,470 --> 00:10:47,990
Then...

265
00:10:48,410 --> 00:10:50,520
why do we suddenly
have to move to Bangkok?

266
00:10:51,370 --> 00:10:52,400
I don't want you to be lonely,

267
00:10:53,490 --> 00:10:55,990
so I want you to live close to your friends.

268
00:10:56,720 --> 00:10:57,240
But...

269
00:10:57,700 --> 00:11:00,800
we can still go back and forth.
We don't have to just stay here.

270
00:11:01,770 --> 00:11:04,310
Then...what about your job?

271
00:11:04,640 --> 00:11:06,510
Oh, I can work remotely.

272
00:11:10,900 --> 00:11:12,120
Thank you, Johan...

273
00:11:13,610 --> 00:11:15,690
for doing so much for me.

274
00:11:16,800 --> 00:11:19,830
But you spent
a lot of money on all this.

275
00:11:21,770 --> 00:11:22,700
And another thing is,

276
00:11:23,340 --> 00:11:24,790
if you're worried about me being lonely,

277
00:11:27,010 --> 00:11:28,010
no need to.

278
00:11:29,350 --> 00:11:31,270
No matter where I look,
you'll be there.

279
00:11:32,350 --> 00:11:33,900
You being with me is enough.

280
00:11:37,190 --> 00:11:38,010
Well,

281
00:11:38,660 --> 00:11:39,910
if you don't like it here,

282
00:11:40,420 --> 00:11:42,690
I'll have Prang sell this place.

283
00:11:42,870 --> 00:11:43,310
And...

284
00:11:44,100 --> 00:11:45,670
can you pretend...

285
00:11:46,000 --> 00:11:48,550
this never happened?

286
00:11:54,400 --> 00:11:55,590
I like it here.

287
00:11:57,010 --> 00:11:57,690
I'm sorry?

288
00:11:59,090 --> 00:12:00,210
I could tell

289
00:12:00,340 --> 00:12:02,990
you decorated the room to my liking.

290
00:12:03,510 --> 00:12:04,400
You knew?

291
00:12:06,260 --> 00:12:06,850
How could I not?

292
00:12:06,880 --> 00:12:08,510
The room screams my name.

293
00:12:09,500 --> 00:12:10,890
As if you read my mind.

294
00:12:20,760 --> 00:12:21,900
I'm okay with

295
00:12:22,190 --> 00:12:24,820
this place becoming our second home.

296
00:12:26,190 --> 00:12:27,900
But from now on,

297
00:12:28,710 --> 00:12:29,800
if anything comes up,

298
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:32,400
can we talk it over together?

299
00:12:34,500 --> 00:12:34,930
Yes.

300
00:12:38,320 --> 00:12:39,390
I love you.

301
00:12:41,110 --> 00:12:42,500
I love you too.

302
00:13:06,010 --> 00:13:07,070
Hello, Maew?

303
00:13:07,630 --> 00:13:09,300
Daotok, are you busy?

304
00:13:09,320 --> 00:13:10,480
You haven't read the group chat.

305
00:13:10,980 --> 00:13:11,980
A little.

306
00:13:13,130 --> 00:13:14,300
But I can talk.

307
00:13:15,100 --> 00:13:16,490
North asked us to go to the beach.

308
00:13:16,590 --> 00:13:17,590
Easter is going.

309
00:13:18,020 --> 00:13:19,320
Are you free?

310
00:13:19,410 --> 00:13:21,310
Tonfah, Johan,
and Hill will also be there.

311
00:13:21,670 --> 00:13:22,980
Ask Arthit to come, too.

312
00:13:23,210 --> 00:13:24,090
Mm...

313
00:13:25,510 --> 00:13:26,410
Mm,

314
00:13:27,150 --> 00:13:28,210
I can go.

315
00:13:29,230 --> 00:13:30,290
Okay,

316
00:13:30,520 --> 00:13:32,600
I'll send you the accommodation
details once I find one.

317
00:14:00,720 --> 00:14:01,540
The water got in my eyes.

318
00:14:03,090 --> 00:14:04,160
I'm already soaked!

319
00:14:08,400 --> 00:14:09,270
Guys.

320
00:14:09,300 --> 00:14:09,840
Hey,

321
00:14:10,310 --> 00:14:10,880
guys.

322
00:14:11,550 --> 00:14:15,080
I overheard North talking to his friends

323
00:14:15,400 --> 00:14:16,960
that they were gonna
spend the night together.

324
00:14:17,340 --> 00:14:19,190
You guys have to promise me

325
00:14:19,500 --> 00:14:21,360
nothing like that's gonna happen.

326
00:14:21,510 --> 00:14:23,200
Go easy on him, would you?

327
00:14:23,360 --> 00:14:25,320
You've been together this long,
and you're still thinking about that?

328
00:14:26,080 --> 00:14:27,110
Johan, you prick.

329
00:14:28,820 --> 00:14:31,810
I'm not a monk, so why would I
abstain from worldly pleasures?

330
00:14:33,800 --> 00:14:34,590
You're right, Arthit.

331
00:14:36,100 --> 00:14:36,820
I'm in.

332
00:14:38,490 --> 00:14:39,520
Whoa!

333
00:14:40,260 --> 00:14:40,990
Tonfah,

334
00:14:42,110 --> 00:14:42,920
are you...

335
00:14:43,050 --> 00:14:45,040
officially shedding your sheep's clothing?

336
00:14:45,330 --> 00:14:46,510
Shit...

337
00:14:46,540 --> 00:14:47,600
I mean...

338
00:14:48,090 --> 00:14:51,820
Typhoon has picked a place
that has enough room for everyone.

339
00:14:51,850 --> 00:14:52,710
Oh...

340
00:14:52,740 --> 00:14:54,210
No need to squeeze into one room.

341
00:14:54,610 --> 00:14:55,610
Is that so?

342
00:14:56,990 --> 00:14:57,990
It is.

343
00:14:58,270 --> 00:14:59,390
I'm not Arthit,

344
00:14:59,420 --> 00:15:01,500
who can't seem
to get his mind out of the gutter.

345
00:15:02,080 --> 00:15:03,390
Well, well, well...

346
00:15:04,210 --> 00:15:06,040
You're lucky it's not raining today,

347
00:15:06,290 --> 00:15:08,710
or Zeus himself would strike
you down for that blatant lie.

348
00:15:09,590 --> 00:15:11,720
You're no different from me.

349
00:15:12,090 --> 00:15:13,270
I can see right through you.

350
00:15:16,360 --> 00:15:17,120
Johan!

351
00:15:26,620 --> 00:15:27,950
They seem to like it here,

352
00:15:28,700 --> 00:15:29,530
especially North.

353
00:15:30,730 --> 00:15:31,410
True.

354
00:15:37,220 --> 00:15:38,290
What do you mean they won't sell it?

355
00:15:39,200 --> 00:15:41,390
Offer them a higher price. Double it, even.

356
00:15:43,240 --> 00:15:44,700
I was just gonna give it to you

357
00:15:45,530 --> 00:15:46,990
as a wedding gift.

358
00:15:48,440 --> 00:15:49,380
Hello, Johan.

359
00:15:51,320 --> 00:15:51,880
Hey...

360
00:15:52,730 --> 00:15:53,800
Don't tell me...

361
00:15:56,590 --> 00:15:57,590
North!

362
00:15:57,620 --> 00:15:58,210
Hey!

363
00:15:58,250 --> 00:15:59,200
Hey, Duennao.

364
00:16:00,840 --> 00:16:01,400
Go!

365
00:16:05,960 --> 00:16:06,720
Not my head.

366
00:16:06,750 --> 00:16:07,550
Don't.

367
00:16:07,760 --> 00:16:08,810
I also just found out

368
00:16:09,670 --> 00:16:10,830
that it belongs to my family.

369
00:16:11,460 --> 00:16:14,050
No need to buy it. I can just
give it to you. It's just one property.

370
00:16:14,800 --> 00:16:15,800
And how did you get here?

371
00:16:16,620 --> 00:16:19,160
The caretakers here remember your faces,

372
00:16:19,430 --> 00:16:20,690
so they called me.

373
00:16:21,300 --> 00:16:24,120
North was mentioned,

374
00:16:24,640 --> 00:16:26,030
so Duennao also wanted to come.

375
00:16:26,060 --> 00:16:27,090
Said he misses his friend.

376
00:16:27,520 --> 00:16:29,460
So how have you been?
It's been a minute.

377
00:16:29,520 --> 00:16:30,750
It's a gap year, man.

378
00:16:30,960 --> 00:16:33,430
I still want to love

379
00:16:33,770 --> 00:16:36,310
without thinking about work or the future.

380
00:16:37,070 --> 00:16:38,220
- How chill.
- Not my head.

381
00:16:38,270 --> 00:16:39,270
Don't.

382
00:16:40,080 --> 00:16:42,020
Man, I was friend-zoned for six years

383
00:16:42,950 --> 00:16:44,040
before I got out of it.

384
00:16:44,440 --> 00:16:45,920
Let me savor the moment.

385
00:16:49,910 --> 00:16:51,490
I heard Arthit say that

386
00:16:51,920 --> 00:16:53,470
this place belongs to your family, right?

387
00:16:54,150 --> 00:16:54,930
That's right.

388
00:16:55,840 --> 00:16:56,800
Mm...

389
00:16:57,200 --> 00:16:58,280
What a coincidence.

390
00:16:58,780 --> 00:17:00,710
Typhoon also chose this place
as our accommodation.

391
00:17:03,660 --> 00:17:05,210
You can always come here.

392
00:17:05,600 --> 00:17:06,520
Make yourself comfortable.

393
00:17:07,700 --> 00:17:08,460
Thank you.

394
00:17:09,300 --> 00:17:11,160
Did you bring a towel for North as well?

395
00:17:11,300 --> 00:17:12,300
I'm gonna give it to him.

396
00:17:15,700 --> 00:17:16,810
Can I have one for Duennao, too?

397
00:17:17,490 --> 00:17:18,200
- Sure.
- Thank you.

398
00:17:18,240 --> 00:17:19,240
Damn you...

399
00:17:20,590 --> 00:17:21,400
One for Easter, too.

400
00:17:22,280 --> 00:17:23,080
Jeez...

401
00:17:25,200 --> 00:17:26,010
Alrighty.

402
00:17:27,490 --> 00:17:28,900
No one but clingy men.

403
00:17:29,390 --> 00:17:30,840
I know, right?

404
00:17:31,130 --> 00:17:32,540
Yeah, so clingy to their boys.

405
00:17:33,600 --> 00:17:34,430
Man,

406
00:17:34,990 --> 00:17:35,990
but you just said...

407
00:17:38,220 --> 00:17:39,890
No need for any fucking towels.

408
00:17:40,410 --> 00:17:41,410
I'll show you how it's done.

409
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:49,210
Arthit?

410
00:17:49,460 --> 00:17:49,990
Huh?

411
00:17:51,440 --> 00:17:53,610
Can you move the bath mat over to me?

412
00:17:54,200 --> 00:17:55,200
I don't wanna soak up the floor.

413
00:18:04,550 --> 00:18:05,540
What's with that grin?

414
00:18:05,850 --> 00:18:07,020
Did you hear what I said?

415
00:18:10,390 --> 00:18:12,080
Why do you look so cute
when you're soaked?

416
00:18:14,130 --> 00:18:15,600
Can you hurry up?

417
00:18:15,640 --> 00:18:16,680
I'm cold.

418
00:18:17,690 --> 00:18:18,470
Arthit!

419
00:18:19,510 --> 00:18:20,580
What are you doing?

420
00:18:21,010 --> 00:18:22,010
Well,

421
00:18:22,240 --> 00:18:23,400
you don't wanna soak up the floor, right?

422
00:18:23,480 --> 00:18:25,400
I didn't ask to be picked up...

423
00:18:25,780 --> 00:18:27,390
There, you're not soaking it up anymore.

424
00:18:29,210 --> 00:18:30,830
You got me here. Now leave.

425
00:18:30,990 --> 00:18:32,300
No way.

426
00:18:32,760 --> 00:18:33,910
What do you mean by that?

427
00:18:34,140 --> 00:18:35,300
I'm taking a shower.

428
00:18:37,400 --> 00:18:39,400
No, let me stay with you.

429
00:18:40,610 --> 00:18:41,900
No.

430
00:18:42,500 --> 00:18:44,800
Why would you ask for that
when I'm taking a shower?

431
00:18:47,700 --> 00:18:48,590
Then...

432
00:18:49,480 --> 00:18:51,100
can I ask for something else?

433
00:18:51,970 --> 00:18:52,710
Arthit!

434
00:18:53,400 --> 00:18:54,560
Please, please, please...

435
00:18:58,120 --> 00:18:59,120
Are you cold?

436
00:18:59,920 --> 00:19:00,700
I'm not.

437
00:19:04,480 --> 00:19:06,830
I'll blow-dry your hair for you.

438
00:19:07,810 --> 00:19:08,500
Alright.

439
00:19:21,670 --> 00:19:22,320
Okay.

440
00:19:37,210 --> 00:19:37,890
Over here.

441
00:19:40,300 --> 00:19:41,300
Is it too hot?

442
00:19:41,330 --> 00:19:42,330
No?

443
00:19:42,900 --> 00:19:43,700
Did you have fun?

444
00:19:45,880 --> 00:19:46,880
Very much so.

445
00:19:47,540 --> 00:19:49,590
It was like I got to be a kid again.

446
00:19:50,590 --> 00:19:52,350
It's such a nice last hurrah

447
00:19:52,530 --> 00:19:55,410
before I start my year-long externship.

448
00:19:58,940 --> 00:19:59,670
Easter,

449
00:20:00,270 --> 00:20:01,110
you know

450
00:20:01,510 --> 00:20:02,510
things will get much harder

451
00:20:02,900 --> 00:20:03,990
after this?

452
00:20:07,850 --> 00:20:08,610
I do.

453
00:20:10,110 --> 00:20:11,410
But I've made my decision,

454
00:20:12,390 --> 00:20:14,000
and I'm going to make it.

455
00:20:30,480 --> 00:20:31,800
I'll always be right by your side

456
00:20:32,790 --> 00:20:34,210
to support you.

457
00:20:38,010 --> 00:20:39,210
I love you, Easter.

458
00:20:42,070 --> 00:20:43,190
I love you too, Hill.

459
00:20:45,930 --> 00:20:47,980
Thank you so much for everything.

460
00:20:59,020 --> 00:21:00,190
With all my pleasure.

461
00:21:22,400 --> 00:21:23,920
Whoa, Johan!

462
00:21:24,340 --> 00:21:25,680
These prawns are huge!

463
00:21:31,890 --> 00:21:33,010
So cute.

464
00:21:34,710 --> 00:21:36,710
I said these prawns are huge...

465
00:21:38,150 --> 00:21:39,200
And I said cute.

466
00:21:40,930 --> 00:21:41,880
The prawns?

467
00:21:42,300 --> 00:21:43,110
You, North.

468
00:21:48,870 --> 00:21:50,890
Johan, go grab the coal.

469
00:21:51,120 --> 00:21:52,710
Johan! Grab the coal, please.

470
00:21:52,740 --> 00:21:54,210
I'm gonna set up the grill.

471
00:21:58,490 --> 00:21:59,280
Let's go.

472
00:21:59,750 --> 00:22:01,000
Everyone's already left.

473
00:22:02,900 --> 00:22:03,690
Suer,

474
00:22:04,060 --> 00:22:05,090
why hurry?

475
00:22:05,360 --> 00:22:06,790
The sunset is so pretty.

476
00:22:13,420 --> 00:22:15,000
I told you to look at the sunset.

477
00:22:15,080 --> 00:22:16,200
It's so pretty.

478
00:22:17,360 --> 00:22:17,980
Well,

479
00:22:18,960 --> 00:22:21,280
there's nothing prettier
than the view right in front of me.

480
00:22:22,990 --> 00:22:23,900
Suer...

481
00:22:24,380 --> 00:22:25,380
I'm serious.

482
00:22:35,360 --> 00:22:36,400
Thank you

483
00:22:37,110 --> 00:22:38,320
for waiting so long for me.

484
00:22:40,420 --> 00:22:41,600
It was a long wait,

485
00:22:42,530 --> 00:22:43,480
but you still waited for me.

486
00:22:49,220 --> 00:22:50,990
I intend to love you
for the rest of my life.

487
00:23:13,950 --> 00:23:15,430
You're the same as always, North.

488
00:23:15,450 --> 00:23:16,520
Come on, it's simple.

489
00:23:16,670 --> 00:23:19,400
You're heartless. These poor things...

490
00:23:19,720 --> 00:23:20,520
Oh, North.

491
00:23:21,020 --> 00:23:23,640
Are you going to live in Bangkok with Johan?

492
00:23:24,760 --> 00:23:25,500
No.

493
00:23:26,010 --> 00:23:28,430
I told him we'd be coming and going.

494
00:23:29,250 --> 00:23:30,600
Since I...

495
00:23:30,830 --> 00:23:32,290
prefer to stay in Chiang Mai.

496
00:23:32,370 --> 00:23:33,210
And it's also

497
00:23:33,400 --> 00:23:34,600
- Mm.
- closer to my mom.

498
00:23:34,630 --> 00:23:35,800
It's not as chaotic either.

499
00:23:37,270 --> 00:23:38,010
The truth is,

500
00:23:38,910 --> 00:23:40,000
Johan bought the condo

501
00:23:40,060 --> 00:23:41,200
because Arthit encouraged him.

502
00:23:41,970 --> 00:23:43,290
He just followed through.

503
00:23:44,290 --> 00:23:46,000
It's not my business, so I'll stay out of it.

504
00:23:49,250 --> 00:23:50,150
Still, it's a good thing.

505
00:23:50,610 --> 00:23:52,020
Now we all live near each other.

506
00:23:58,530 --> 00:23:59,200
Hey!

507
00:23:59,410 --> 00:24:00,190
North!

508
00:24:01,180 --> 00:24:02,180
What's wrong?

509
00:24:05,290 --> 00:24:06,200
Aw, North.

510
00:24:07,740 --> 00:24:09,000
I missed you.

511
00:24:10,360 --> 00:24:12,300
You're crying? That's crazy.

512
00:24:13,120 --> 00:24:15,240
Aww...

513
00:24:17,330 --> 00:24:20,000
I missed you too.

514
00:24:21,130 --> 00:24:23,480
Back then, we used to see
each other every day.

515
00:24:24,310 --> 00:24:26,480
When we each moved in with
our boyfriends,

516
00:24:26,830 --> 00:24:28,200
I was already heartbroken.

517
00:24:28,510 --> 00:24:29,790
But you...

518
00:24:29,990 --> 00:24:31,670
moved all the way to Bangkok.

519
00:24:32,400 --> 00:24:34,900
Although I had a boyfriend,
I still missed you.

520
00:24:38,690 --> 00:24:39,690
North.

521
00:24:41,450 --> 00:24:44,980
Well, I also missed the cutting board bed.

522
00:24:45,010 --> 00:24:46,890
Yeah, the cutting board bed.

523
00:24:51,530 --> 00:24:52,880
The cutting board...

524
00:24:52,960 --> 00:24:53,830
North.

525
00:24:56,900 --> 00:24:58,090
I forgot...

526
00:24:59,500 --> 00:25:01,810
I forgot to tell Johan that
tonight we'll sleep...

527
00:25:02,140 --> 00:25:03,140
- No.
- No.

528
00:25:07,000 --> 00:25:07,610
What?

529
00:25:12,070 --> 00:25:12,660
North,

530
00:25:13,240 --> 00:25:14,310
can you not sleep with anyone else?

531
00:25:15,770 --> 00:25:17,110
You sleep with me every night.

532
00:25:17,610 --> 00:25:19,080
How am I supposed to sleep without you?

533
00:25:22,740 --> 00:25:23,350
Yes, Hill.

534
00:25:24,750 --> 00:25:26,550
I'll sleep with you tonight.

535
00:25:29,130 --> 00:25:29,800
What the hell?

536
00:25:31,320 --> 00:25:32,200
Oh, then...

537
00:25:33,340 --> 00:25:34,400
Alright, Johan.

538
00:25:40,410 --> 00:25:41,900
Well, well, well.

539
00:25:42,500 --> 00:25:43,800
You keep roasting me,

540
00:25:43,940 --> 00:25:45,740
but you're all whipped for them too,
a**holes.

541
00:25:46,790 --> 00:25:47,790
Whoa, what did he bring?

542
00:25:48,130 --> 00:25:50,230
Wow, Maew, that looks tasty.

543
00:25:50,260 --> 00:25:51,260
Wow.

544
00:25:52,100 --> 00:25:53,680
- Whoa, Daotok.
- Is that Miang talay?

545
00:25:53,710 --> 00:25:55,970
When did you become this good at cooking?

546
00:25:56,510 --> 00:25:57,790
Maew did all this.

547
00:25:58,830 --> 00:25:59,540
Thought so.

548
00:25:59,570 --> 00:26:01,690
Maew's food always looks delicious.

549
00:26:01,720 --> 00:26:02,760
Looks good?

550
00:26:02,790 --> 00:26:03,790
Yes.

551
00:26:04,120 --> 00:26:05,700
That's my boyfriend for you.

552
00:26:05,940 --> 00:26:06,600
Amazing, right?

553
00:26:06,990 --> 00:26:07,910
Yes.

554
00:26:09,590 --> 00:26:10,720
Wow, Tonfah,

555
00:26:11,040 --> 00:26:13,160
since when are you like this?

556
00:26:13,220 --> 00:26:15,510
- Well...Arthit had an influence on me.
- Come on...

557
00:26:15,580 --> 00:26:16,590
Arthit did?

558
00:26:16,760 --> 00:26:18,480
- What?
- It's always Arthit, huh?

559
00:26:18,710 --> 00:26:19,810
- I didn't do anything.
- Well, well.

560
00:26:21,580 --> 00:26:22,690
What are we waiting for? Let's eat.

561
00:26:22,830 --> 00:26:24,010
Is there anything else you want?

562
00:26:24,800 --> 00:26:25,410
Yes.

563
00:26:25,520 --> 00:26:26,090
What is it?

564
00:26:26,190 --> 00:26:28,160
I want you two to come sit and eat already.

565
00:26:28,250 --> 00:26:29,630
Come. Let's eat, I'm hungry.

566
00:26:29,660 --> 00:26:30,710
Mm, me too.

567
00:26:30,740 --> 00:26:31,920
- Quickly.
- Fine.

568
00:26:32,200 --> 00:26:34,190
Well then,
thanks for the meal, everyone.

569
00:26:34,400 --> 00:26:36,170
- Spin that plate for me.
- Yes, Suer.

570
00:26:36,190 --> 00:26:37,080
Yeah, I'm hungry as f*ck.

571
00:26:37,110 --> 00:26:38,510
Eat your greens

572
00:26:38,550 --> 00:26:39,600
since you've been constipated lately.

573
00:26:39,640 --> 00:26:40,660
Eat this.

574
00:27:00,500 --> 00:27:01,390
Should we play a game?

575
00:27:02,970 --> 00:27:04,390
Sure, what game?

576
00:27:05,300 --> 00:27:06,390
How about this one?

577
00:27:07,520 --> 00:27:08,810
'Answer quickly, or else...'

578
00:27:09,170 --> 00:27:10,560
Let's start with you, North.

579
00:27:10,800 --> 00:27:11,470
Me?

580
00:27:11,670 --> 00:27:12,450
Mm.

581
00:27:12,640 --> 00:27:13,510
What do you want me to do?

582
00:27:13,830 --> 00:27:15,170
What do you wanna say to Johan?

583
00:27:22,490 --> 00:27:23,100
I...

584
00:27:25,250 --> 00:27:26,280
I love you, Johan.

585
00:27:26,310 --> 00:27:28,040
- Wow!
- Wow!

586
00:27:28,080 --> 00:27:30,080
You took an easy way out, boo!

587
00:27:32,070 --> 00:27:33,130
Alright, your turn.

588
00:27:33,350 --> 00:27:34,380
Ask away.

589
00:27:35,080 --> 00:27:36,080
Uh, my turn?

590
00:27:37,390 --> 00:27:38,510
I'll ask Arthit.

591
00:27:38,950 --> 00:27:39,600
Huh?

592
00:27:40,250 --> 00:27:41,200
What the hell, North?

593
00:27:41,350 --> 00:27:41,960
Hey.

594
00:27:42,680 --> 00:27:44,300
Hey, hey, hey!

595
00:27:44,620 --> 00:27:45,620
Let's go with this one.

596
00:27:46,400 --> 00:27:47,980
Anything you wanna say to Daotok?

597
00:27:52,350 --> 00:27:53,020
- Whoa!
- Huh?

598
00:27:53,260 --> 00:27:54,260
- Arthit, you!
- Whoa...

599
00:27:54,650 --> 00:27:56,700
I told you to "say" something,

600
00:27:57,260 --> 00:27:58,140
not "do" something!

601
00:27:58,530 --> 00:27:59,000
Really?

602
00:28:00,010 --> 00:28:00,680
My bad.

603
00:28:01,180 --> 00:28:02,480
I jumped the gun.

604
00:28:02,510 --> 00:28:03,660
Jeez, you...

605
00:28:05,070 --> 00:28:05,700
Alright,

606
00:28:06,630 --> 00:28:07,490
my turn?

607
00:28:07,850 --> 00:28:08,600
Then...

608
00:28:09,200 --> 00:28:10,410
I'll ask...

609
00:28:11,460 --> 00:28:12,480
Easter.

610
00:28:13,310 --> 00:28:13,890
Yes?

611
00:28:15,150 --> 00:28:17,400
I wanna ask...

612
00:28:18,240 --> 00:28:19,300
if Hill

613
00:28:20,070 --> 00:28:21,970
gets clingy when he's around you?

614
00:28:22,080 --> 00:28:23,080
Arthit.

615
00:28:23,220 --> 00:28:24,110
What?

616
00:28:24,650 --> 00:28:26,390
It's a game, right?

617
00:28:26,810 --> 00:28:27,580
Shit.

618
00:28:27,940 --> 00:28:29,650
When it's just the two of us,

619
00:28:29,970 --> 00:28:30,970
he gets really clingy,

620
00:28:31,130 --> 00:28:33,390
like a little baby...

621
00:28:37,100 --> 00:28:38,020
Show-off.

622
00:28:38,800 --> 00:28:39,710
Wait, wait, wait...

623
00:28:40,240 --> 00:28:41,000
That's it?

624
00:28:43,140 --> 00:28:44,820
Aw, you're no fun.

625
00:28:45,700 --> 00:28:46,430
Okay,

626
00:28:47,070 --> 00:28:47,790
my turn, right?

627
00:28:48,520 --> 00:28:49,430
I'll ask Tiger.

628
00:28:51,600 --> 00:28:53,400
What made you decide

629
00:28:53,800 --> 00:28:55,790
to confess your love to Duennao

630
00:28:55,930 --> 00:28:58,680
after being friends for six years?

631
00:28:59,890 --> 00:29:01,710
I guess I just thought that...

632
00:29:02,220 --> 00:29:03,240
I couldn't let him go.

633
00:29:03,360 --> 00:29:05,610
- Aww.
- Aww.

634
00:29:06,690 --> 00:29:08,200
If I hadn't told him then,

635
00:29:10,210 --> 00:29:11,880
I would've regretted it
for the rest of my life.

636
00:29:12,120 --> 00:29:15,600
Ooohhh, that much, huh?

637
00:29:16,180 --> 00:29:16,920
Let me be real.

638
00:29:16,970 --> 00:29:19,100
As someone who's seen
you guys since day one,

639
00:29:20,510 --> 00:29:21,310
I can honestly say

640
00:29:21,590 --> 00:29:22,890
I'm so damn touched.

641
00:29:26,420 --> 00:29:28,280
Enough. Stop the tearjerker.

642
00:29:30,280 --> 00:29:31,480
It's your turn now, Suer.

643
00:29:33,690 --> 00:29:35,000
Hm...

644
00:29:35,250 --> 00:29:36,180
Then...

645
00:29:36,300 --> 00:29:37,760
I'll ask Typhoon.

646
00:29:38,300 --> 00:29:38,710
Hm?

647
00:29:39,930 --> 00:29:40,960
Give me a sentence

648
00:29:41,360 --> 00:29:43,400
that brings tears to your eyes
just thinking about it.

649
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:47,000
Like, what kind of tears?

650
00:29:47,290 --> 00:29:49,400
Sad tears or happy tears?

651
00:29:49,690 --> 00:29:51,510
Just enough to make you choke up.

652
00:29:51,750 --> 00:29:53,780
Hm...

653
00:29:55,430 --> 00:29:58,130
"Typhoon, you're like a little brother,
someone very important to me."

654
00:30:00,700 --> 00:30:02,190
Tonfah, you're done.

655
00:30:04,240 --> 00:30:05,100
Typhoon,

656
00:30:05,350 --> 00:30:06,920
let's not talk about that anymore.

657
00:30:08,120 --> 00:30:09,220
I'm just teasing you.

658
00:30:12,200 --> 00:30:13,090
Duennao,

659
00:30:13,120 --> 00:30:15,110
this isn't fun anymore.

660
00:30:15,150 --> 00:30:17,520
How about we find something else to do?

661
00:30:17,770 --> 00:30:18,690
Sure thing.

662
00:30:19,060 --> 00:30:19,740
What should it be?

663
00:30:29,650 --> 00:30:30,830
Thank you

664
00:30:33,900 --> 00:30:36,410
for joining my club that day.

665
00:30:37,620 --> 00:30:38,620
Hey, Easter.

666
00:30:39,480 --> 00:30:41,530
Are you sure we're at the right place?

667
00:30:41,570 --> 00:30:42,420
Hi!

668
00:30:44,890 --> 00:30:45,890
Whoa, here he is!

669
00:30:46,890 --> 00:30:47,770
Otherwise...

670
00:30:47,800 --> 00:30:48,800
Whoa, not me!

671
00:30:48,830 --> 00:30:50,490
I don't know

672
00:30:51,230 --> 00:30:54,200
how my life could be this happy right now.

673
00:30:56,210 --> 00:30:57,210
Jeez...

674
00:30:57,440 --> 00:30:58,440
Thank North.

675
00:30:59,300 --> 00:31:00,510
Without him,

676
00:31:01,030 --> 00:31:02,620
how would we even have met?

677
00:31:05,890 --> 00:31:06,890
- North.
- Huh?

678
00:31:10,990 --> 00:31:12,090
Thank you

679
00:31:13,350 --> 00:31:15,450
for bringing us together.

680
00:31:20,710 --> 00:31:22,120
Maew, what was that about?

681
00:31:23,970 --> 00:31:24,780
Don't cry.

682
00:31:25,300 --> 00:31:26,000
Nope.

683
00:31:26,030 --> 00:31:27,370
Maew, don't cry.

684
00:31:27,400 --> 00:31:29,200
- He's pouting.
- Maew...

685
00:31:32,040 --> 00:31:33,840
Without all of you,

686
00:31:34,590 --> 00:31:35,810
I might never have...

687
00:31:36,270 --> 00:31:38,490
gone back and talked to Tonfah again.

688
00:31:41,260 --> 00:31:43,680
Actually, I want to thank all of you

689
00:31:44,500 --> 00:31:47,200
for bringing so much color into my life.

690
00:31:47,800 --> 00:31:50,200
Even though North turned
my drawing club

691
00:31:51,100 --> 00:31:52,000
into a noisy

692
00:31:52,810 --> 00:31:54,400
and chaotic place,

693
00:31:55,560 --> 00:31:57,600
I'm still grateful to everyone

694
00:31:58,300 --> 00:32:00,180
for walking through that door.

695
00:32:04,300 --> 00:32:05,000
North,

696
00:32:06,540 --> 00:32:07,800
I also thank you

697
00:32:08,820 --> 00:32:10,640
for being right next to Suer

698
00:32:11,410 --> 00:32:13,100
when I was still dumb.

699
00:32:14,520 --> 00:32:16,040
At least you kept him company

700
00:32:17,020 --> 00:32:19,110
while he was waiting for me.

701
00:32:19,230 --> 00:32:20,720
Dude, what are you guys saying?

702
00:32:22,070 --> 00:32:23,700
Damn, these tearjerking scenes...

703
00:32:23,740 --> 00:32:24,510
Mm!

704
00:32:25,700 --> 00:32:26,490
I'm drunk!

705
00:32:26,600 --> 00:32:27,400
Yeah.

706
00:32:30,060 --> 00:32:30,830
Jeez...

707
00:32:30,860 --> 00:32:33,100
Well, we're friends, right?

708
00:32:33,910 --> 00:32:35,310
- Mm.
- Mm...

709
00:32:35,690 --> 00:32:36,310
Thank you.

710
00:32:36,340 --> 00:32:37,000
Thank you.

711
00:32:37,040 --> 00:32:38,500
- Thank you, really.
- Thanks.

712
00:32:39,210 --> 00:32:40,890
I love you guys, too.

713
00:32:41,340 --> 00:32:42,160
Love you guys so much.

714
00:32:42,190 --> 00:32:43,730
Me too.

715
00:32:43,760 --> 00:32:46,800
I don't think Easter has changed
since the day I first met him.

716
00:32:47,300 --> 00:32:48,110
Likewise,

717
00:32:48,350 --> 00:32:49,810
North is still the same
as when we first met.

718
00:32:50,840 --> 00:32:51,800
I'm happy.

719
00:32:52,400 --> 00:32:53,810
I don't have to
steal a glance at him anymore.

720
00:32:55,400 --> 00:32:56,340
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

721
00:32:56,370 --> 00:32:58,190
- Who started this?
- Cheers.

722
00:32:58,560 --> 00:32:59,560
I totally get it.

723
00:33:00,650 --> 00:33:02,110
That feeling...

724
00:33:02,370 --> 00:33:03,660
when all you can do is watch.

725
00:33:05,510 --> 00:33:07,000
But good things

726
00:33:07,600 --> 00:33:09,410
come to those who wait, right?

727
00:33:10,600 --> 00:33:11,210
Hey,

728
00:33:11,610 --> 00:33:14,200
what the fuck are you all waiting for, huh?

729
00:33:14,530 --> 00:33:15,500
Look at me.

730
00:33:15,820 --> 00:33:17,430
All I did was knock on his door,

731
00:33:17,500 --> 00:33:18,800
and I got right into his room.

732
00:33:19,400 --> 00:33:21,190
Yeah, how about that?

733
00:33:21,750 --> 00:33:23,900
I'm the fucking GOAT, man.

734
00:33:24,000 --> 00:33:24,900
What the fuck do you mean?

735
00:33:24,970 --> 00:33:26,030
Bathroom? Bedroom?

736
00:33:26,100 --> 00:33:27,510
Johan, you a**hole.

737
00:33:31,600 --> 00:33:33,670
You're drunk, but you're still drinking?

738
00:33:34,990 --> 00:33:37,420
I think the boys
are already getting so drunk.

739
00:33:37,980 --> 00:33:39,500
Should we call it a night
and get some rest?

740
00:33:49,290 --> 00:33:50,900
Where are we going?

741
00:33:51,390 --> 00:33:52,210
To our room.

742
00:33:55,410 --> 00:33:56,460
We're by the bed now.

743
00:33:56,480 --> 00:33:57,210
Easy, get down slowly.

744
00:33:57,920 --> 00:34:00,090
No. I don't want to.

745
00:34:01,630 --> 00:34:02,790
My love...

746
00:34:03,510 --> 00:34:05,290
I want to hug you.

747
00:34:06,600 --> 00:34:07,880
You are hugging me,

748
00:34:08,420 --> 00:34:09,120
aren't you?

749
00:34:10,670 --> 00:34:11,890
I want to kiss your cheek, too.

750
00:34:14,810 --> 00:34:15,810
Duennao.

751
00:34:17,220 --> 00:34:18,910
I love you, Suer.

752
00:34:22,100 --> 00:34:24,010
I love you so much.

753
00:34:24,050 --> 00:34:24,790
Be careful.

754
00:34:35,500 --> 00:34:37,310
I love you so much, too.

755
00:35:09,200 --> 00:35:10,320
No more.

756
00:35:13,110 --> 00:35:14,110
No more what?

757
00:35:15,190 --> 00:35:16,190
I just...

758
00:35:17,080 --> 00:35:18,890
I just want to hug you.

759
00:35:20,230 --> 00:35:21,380
I don't know.

760
00:35:21,870 --> 00:35:23,110
You're acting suspicious.

761
00:35:24,570 --> 00:35:25,130
Sure.

762
00:35:25,930 --> 00:35:28,810
I just want to hug you, really.

763
00:35:32,910 --> 00:35:33,590
Hey.

764
00:35:39,000 --> 00:35:40,000
What is it?

765
00:35:41,570 --> 00:35:44,010
I want to keep looking at you like this
for the rest of my life.

766
00:35:46,620 --> 00:35:49,010
Will you stay and let me
look at you like this forever?

767
00:35:50,160 --> 00:35:52,390
It's not like I'm going anywhere.

768
00:36:07,030 --> 00:36:08,600
Didn't you say you just wanted a hug?

769
00:36:10,750 --> 00:36:12,310
Why?

770
00:36:18,660 --> 00:36:19,980
Come on, just a little extra.

771
00:36:20,500 --> 00:36:21,500
Just a little.

772
00:36:23,430 --> 00:36:25,910
Please, please, please, please.

773
00:36:26,510 --> 00:36:27,720
Pretty please?

774
00:36:28,650 --> 00:36:29,320
Please?

775
00:36:33,280 --> 00:36:34,280
You're just too cute.

776
00:37:12,710 --> 00:37:13,390
Um...

777
00:37:13,420 --> 00:37:14,310
Johan?

778
00:37:14,850 --> 00:37:16,180
If all I wanted was sleep,

779
00:37:16,220 --> 00:37:17,410
I would've let you sleep with your friends.

780
00:37:17,790 --> 00:37:18,980
What do you mean?

781
00:37:24,340 --> 00:37:25,340
Can I?

782
00:37:26,340 --> 00:37:27,340
Mm...

783
00:37:27,390 --> 00:37:28,390
I don't know.

784
00:37:29,800 --> 00:37:30,700
Good boy.

785
00:38:18,280 --> 00:38:19,800
Are you falling for me again?

786
00:38:21,020 --> 00:38:22,120
You're getting ahead of yourself.

787
00:38:23,200 --> 00:38:24,800
I'm not falling for you.

788
00:38:28,880 --> 00:38:30,190
Don't you love me anymore?

789
00:38:32,250 --> 00:38:33,710
I only fell for you once.

790
00:38:36,010 --> 00:38:37,290
I never managed to climb back out.

791
00:38:42,790 --> 00:38:44,840
Who taught you to say things like that?

792
00:38:45,320 --> 00:38:45,880
Hm?

793
00:38:47,010 --> 00:38:47,940
Why?

794
00:38:54,300 --> 00:38:55,220
It's cute.

795
00:39:00,480 --> 00:39:01,480
Hill...

796
00:39:14,140 --> 00:39:14,900
Tonfah.

797
00:39:15,290 --> 00:39:15,770
Yes?

798
00:39:20,440 --> 00:39:22,110
You're still not tired of this model?

799
00:39:25,240 --> 00:39:26,090
Nope.

800
00:39:26,960 --> 00:39:28,030
What about you, Tonfah?

801
00:39:28,680 --> 00:39:30,000
Not tired of this cameraman yet?

802
00:39:33,620 --> 00:39:35,000
For me,

803
00:39:35,500 --> 00:39:37,190
I'll keep smiling for this cameraman

804
00:39:37,610 --> 00:39:38,690
for the rest of my life.

805
00:39:50,360 --> 00:39:53,000
Maew still loves taking photos of Tonfah

806
00:39:53,050 --> 00:39:54,680
- more than anything in this world.
- Three...

807
00:39:54,830 --> 00:39:56,320
Two… One…

808
00:39:57,410 --> 00:39:58,410
As for Tiger,

809
00:39:58,600 --> 00:40:02,020
he does everything he and Duennao
used to do as friends.

810
00:40:02,330 --> 00:40:03,700
But now he does
what he used to only imagine,

811
00:40:03,740 --> 00:40:05,200
- things he wasn't brave enough
- Come on.

812
00:40:05,430 --> 00:40:07,000
to do before.

813
00:40:08,530 --> 00:40:09,290
Out of practice?

814
00:40:09,320 --> 00:40:10,830
Yeah, I'm old now.

815
00:40:24,180 --> 00:40:24,650
Hey!

816
00:40:25,470 --> 00:40:26,510
Suer!

817
00:40:27,100 --> 00:40:28,240
You're doing this again.

818
00:40:28,410 --> 00:40:29,100
What?

819
00:40:29,220 --> 00:40:30,310
- I'm not doing anything.
- Hey!

820
00:40:30,400 --> 00:40:31,490
What are you doing?

821
00:40:33,090 --> 00:40:34,940
I'm just...

822
00:40:35,350 --> 00:40:37,080
doing what I want to do.

823
00:40:38,120 --> 00:40:39,220
Don't tell me...

824
00:40:39,910 --> 00:40:41,920
Ever since we started
playing soccer together,

825
00:40:42,840 --> 00:40:44,770
you've always had dirty thoughts about me?

826
00:40:45,080 --> 00:40:46,080
Well, I used to like you.

827
00:40:46,320 --> 00:40:46,970
Hey!

828
00:40:52,180 --> 00:40:52,820
Let go.

829
00:40:54,040 --> 00:40:55,640
I've always wanted to do this.

830
00:40:57,540 --> 00:40:58,820
You are such a...

831
00:41:00,610 --> 00:41:02,410
Thank you for letting me love you.

832
00:41:05,830 --> 00:41:06,230
Hey.

833
00:41:07,260 --> 00:41:08,870
- I'll get you back, Suer.
- Oh, yeah?

834
00:41:08,900 --> 00:41:10,460
Come on, then. Come on.

835
00:41:10,500 --> 00:41:12,510
Catch me if you can, hm?

836
00:41:14,390 --> 00:41:15,420
As for Arthit,

837
00:41:15,670 --> 00:41:16,670
he talks big

838
00:41:16,840 --> 00:41:18,610
but is a nervous wreck.

839
00:41:18,910 --> 00:41:22,310
He's looking for a chance
to propose to Daotok.

840
00:41:22,350 --> 00:41:23,810
Everything is already set.

841
00:41:23,840 --> 00:41:25,050
He even bought

842
00:41:25,100 --> 00:41:27,020
tickets to San Francisco for everyone

843
00:41:27,040 --> 00:41:28,860
to go and celebrate there.

844
00:41:28,900 --> 00:41:30,400
The only thing is...

845
00:41:37,840 --> 00:41:38,720
F*ck...

846
00:41:41,810 --> 00:41:42,890
What are you doing?

847
00:41:43,000 --> 00:41:43,690
Oh.

848
00:41:44,900 --> 00:41:45,900
Um...

849
00:41:46,600 --> 00:41:47,870
I'm feeding the fish.

850
00:41:49,050 --> 00:41:49,730
Yeah.

851
00:41:53,000 --> 00:41:54,000
That's beautiful.

852
00:41:55,310 --> 00:41:56,180
You're cute.

853
00:41:57,940 --> 00:41:59,980
He still hasn't proposed.

854
00:42:00,540 --> 00:42:01,690
He's such a chicken.

855
00:42:02,030 --> 00:42:03,120
Go in, move, move.

856
00:42:03,290 --> 00:42:05,300
- As for North... Oh! That's me.
- That's it. Plant it.

857
00:42:05,990 --> 00:42:08,090
- As for North, he goes back and forth
- Good job.

858
00:42:08,120 --> 00:42:09,690
- between Bangkok and Chiang Mai.
- Good.

859
00:42:09,770 --> 00:42:10,640
- Most importantly,
- Behind you.

860
00:42:10,670 --> 00:42:12,820
he's training to become
a national e-sports athlete.

861
00:42:12,860 --> 00:42:15,510
To make use of
the seven-figure equipment Johan bought.

862
00:42:16,710 --> 00:42:18,900
But even though this athlete looks cute,

863
00:42:18,930 --> 00:42:21,200
he already has his own sweetheart.

864
00:42:21,240 --> 00:42:23,300
So don't try to hit on him.

865
00:42:24,450 --> 00:42:26,920
As for my best
cutting board bed buddy, Easter,

866
00:42:27,180 --> 00:42:28,580
he graduated from veterinary school.

867
00:42:28,610 --> 00:42:29,990
But he said he won't

868
00:42:30,030 --> 00:42:31,640
fully commit to working as a vet.

869
00:42:31,670 --> 00:42:34,510
Hill and Easter plan to adopt a child
and raise them together.

870
00:42:34,550 --> 00:42:35,400
Wow.

871
00:42:35,440 --> 00:42:37,490
Just imagining it melts my heart.

872
00:42:37,510 --> 00:42:39,300
North, when will you be ready?

873
00:42:39,900 --> 00:42:41,810
If you let Maew set it up,
it'd be done by now.

874
00:42:42,070 --> 00:42:43,960
Yeah, I know. Just a sec.

875
00:42:44,440 --> 00:42:45,390
I'll set it to auto.

876
00:42:45,990 --> 00:42:46,800
Ready?

877
00:42:46,980 --> 00:42:47,570
Yes.

878
00:42:48,510 --> 00:42:49,400
Everyone, get in the frame.

879
00:42:49,740 --> 00:42:50,280
Okay.

880
00:42:50,900 --> 00:42:51,520
Come.

881
00:42:52,250 --> 00:42:53,070
Hurry, North!

882
00:42:53,390 --> 00:42:54,700
You don't look ready.

883
00:42:55,010 --> 00:42:55,820
Okay now?

884
00:42:56,530 --> 00:42:58,800
One, two, three!

885
00:42:58,930 --> 00:42:59,710
Johan, let's go.

886
00:43:00,540 --> 00:43:01,090
- Hurry!
- Let's go.

887
00:43:01,110 --> 00:43:01,400
Come, North.

888
00:43:01,420 --> 00:43:02,830
- Everyone always thanks me.
- Hurry, run over here!

889
00:43:02,870 --> 00:43:05,280
for being the one who brought us together.

890
00:43:05,530 --> 00:43:06,320
To be honest,

891
00:43:06,760 --> 00:43:07,320
I feel

892
00:43:07,500 --> 00:43:09,380
very honored to have that role,

893
00:43:09,520 --> 00:43:11,170
because I'm just as glad

894
00:43:11,440 --> 00:43:13,440
to have all of them by my side.

895
00:43:14,180 --> 00:43:15,180
From now on,

896
00:43:15,370 --> 00:43:17,310
no matter how much older we become

897
00:43:17,430 --> 00:43:18,890
or what we choose to do,

898
00:43:19,040 --> 00:43:20,900
we will always have each other.

899
00:43:20,930 --> 00:43:24,200
I'm glad that fate brought us all together.

900
00:43:24,280 --> 00:43:25,230
I love you all so much.
